        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 1 at 10:55PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1054 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Nara Visa, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Oldham
and south central Hartley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
